                <h3>How to use Tinatapi</h3>
                <p>
                    You don't need to signup or have an API key to use Tinatapi - just call a URL via REST and receive a response in JSON.
                </p>
                
                <h4>Fetch information about every country</h4>
                <p class="well well-code">
                    <span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries">/countries.json</a> - Get information about every country in a single request.
                </p>
            
                <h4>Fetch information about a specific country</h4>            
                
                <h5>By ISO identifier</h5>
                <p>Use <strong>/countries/{ISO-identifier}.json</strong> to get information about a country using it's 2 or 3 character ISO identifier or number.</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/US/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/USA">/countries/USA.json</a> - Get information about the United States</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/RU/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/RU">/countries/RU.json</a> - Get information about Russia</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/CN/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/156">/countries/156.json</a> - Get information about China</p>
                
                <h5>By country name</h5>
                <p>Although using an ISO code is recommended you can also reference countries by name.</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/ZA/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/South_Africa">/countries/South_Africa.json</a> - Get information about South Africa</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/IR/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/Iran">/countries/Iran.json</a> - Get information about Iran</p>                                
                <p>Countries can be looked up by known aliases. For example "<a href="/countries/United_Kingdom">United Kingdom</a>", "<a href="/countries/Britain">Britain</a>", "<a href="/countries/Great_Britain">Great Britain</a>" all point to the <a href="/countries/UK">UK</a>.</p>
                
                <h5>National flags</h5>
                <p>You can also look up national flags (as SVG images) by ISO code, country name or alias.</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/FR/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/France/flag">/countries/France/flag.svg</a> - Get the French flag</p>
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/GB/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code"><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/GB/flag">/countries/GB/flag.svg</a> - Get the British flag</p>                
                <div id="flag" class="flag hidden-xs pull-left" style="height: 50px; width: 55px; margin: 4px 10px; background-image: url(/countries/IN/flag.svg);"></div>
                <p class="well well-code "><span class="text-muted">api.tinata.co.uk</span><a href="/countries/356/flag">/countries/356/flag.svg</a> - Get the Indian flag</p>
